    <h1>The Method of Multiple Working Hypotheses</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">T. C. Chamberlin · 1890 · Science · <a href="https://web.stanford.edu/dept/EHS/training/Chamberlin1890.pdf">PDF (Stanford)</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Hold multiple hypotheses simultaneously, or your favorite will blind you. The single "ruling theory" breeds parental affection; multiple working hypotheses breed impartiality.</p>
    </div>

