      <li><a href="/reading/scientific-method/popper-1934/">Popper 1934</a> — falsifiability as the elimination mechanism Chamberlin left implicit</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/scientific-method/fisher-1935/">Fisher 1935</a> — the statistical machinery for actually testing hypotheses</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/scientific-method/platt-1964/">Platt 1964</a> — strong inference extends Chamberlin: design experiments that discriminate between hypotheses</li>
